story.storykicker: Pass percentage may have gone down but more number of students score above 90 per cent in Maharashtra HSC
story.storybody:
Maharashtra State Board of Secondary and Higher Secondary Education (MSBSHSE) announced the results along with handing over reports and scores to individuals on Friday, i.e. June 3. This time there are more number of students who scored above 90's, however, the over all pass percentage has dropped down in comparison to what it was in the previous year.

(Read: Open University admissions to begin online )

Marks scored by students:

ML Dahunkar College, Vile Parle: 24 students of this college have scored above 90 per cent, still the over all pass percentage decreased from last year. Last year 99.8 per cent students passed the exam, while this year the pass percentage was 98 per cent.

As many as 55 per cent of the students have scored a distinction.

Birla College, Kalyan: There was a rise in the number of students, who scored pretty well, here as well. Commerce stream had 8-9 students who scored above 90 per cent.

Science stream had more than ten students who scored above 90 per cent.

(Read: DU admissions: Now adding vocational subjects for calculating BFS allowed in BA, BCom (prog) )

One of the students from Birla College also scored 197 in Maharashtra Common Entrance Test.

VG Vaze College, Mulund: Students performed, more or less the same as last year. About 647 out of 1438 students bagged distinctions.

The highest score in Commerce increased to 93.23 per cent, while that in Arts and Science fell down by a few points

SIES College of Science, Arts and Commerce, Sion: As many as 181 students in the Science stream scored above 90 per cent, which was last year 250 students.

Arts stream had 77 students, who scored above 90 per cent, while 97 students had scored the same last year.
